1
00:00:21,100 --> 00:00:23,020
We're with you!

2
00:00:23,100 --> 00:00:24,390
Let's go!

3
00:00:24,890 --> 00:00:27,020
There are about 350 people.

4
00:00:27,770 --> 00:00:31,320
Out of which only about 100
actually know how to fight.

5
00:00:31,820 --> 00:00:34,740
Get an exact number later on.

6
00:00:36,450 --> 00:00:40,160
Are we seriously going to do this, Boss?

7
00:00:41,410 --> 00:00:44,290
The master is bent on doing it.

8
00:00:44,370 --> 00:00:46,000
We have no choice.

9
00:00:49,040 --> 00:00:51,380
They must be insane.

10
00:00:52,340 --> 00:00:56,590
Do these guys think they have a chance
against the king's army?

11
00:00:57,590 --> 00:01:00,970
All of them owe the master money.

12
00:01:01,060 --> 00:01:05,730
He assembled them by saying that
he'll write it off if they fight.

13
00:01:06,480 --> 00:01:10,610
Even still, they wouldn't have come
if they knew their enemy was the king.

14
00:01:10,690 --> 00:01:12,650
But now that they're here,
they can't turn back

15
00:01:12,730 --> 00:01:15,400
because their pride
as a Nordic man won't allow that.

16
00:01:16,740 --> 00:01:19,950
And plus, people feel
invincible in big numbers.

17
00:01:20,450 --> 00:01:22,700
It makes you feel like you can win.

18
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:26,460
It was a smart tactic
to wait until everyone assembled

19
00:01:26,540 --> 00:01:28,370
before saying our enemy is the king.

20
00:01:31,630 --> 00:01:36,010
I didn't know Thorgil was this battlewise.

21
00:01:56,400 --> 00:02:00,030
<i>The master is determined to do it.</i>
<i>He's already got an army.</i>

22
00:02:01,410 --> 00:02:04,330
This place is going to
become a battlefield.

23
00:02:06,450 --> 00:02:09,920
I told you, didn't I?
We have to leave this farm now

24
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:12,420
or we'll get caught up in it, Thorfinn.

25
00:02:13,380 --> 00:02:15,920
I know, but…

26
00:02:26,060 --> 00:02:27,350
Leif,

27
00:02:29,730 --> 00:02:33,520
we cannot leave Arnheid like this

28
00:02:33,610 --> 00:02:35,940
and escape from the farm.

29
00:02:37,780 --> 00:02:41,490
Thank you so much

30
00:02:42,450 --> 00:02:44,740
for caring about someone like me.

31
00:02:47,870 --> 00:02:50,160
You've changed, Thorfinn.

32
00:02:51,370 --> 00:02:54,750
At first, when I saw you,
I thought you were the wrong person.

33
00:02:58,420 --> 00:03:02,050
You look much better now, Thorfinn.

34
00:03:07,770 --> 00:03:11,390
I finally got to see you again.
I can't just

35
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:14,860
leave you and escape on my own.

36
00:03:17,650 --> 00:03:19,070
Pater, there it is again!

37
00:03:19,150 --> 00:03:20,820
Turn her to the side.

38
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:23,490
We can't let her choke on
whatever she's coughing up.

39
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:25,990
Pater,

40
00:03:26,490 --> 00:03:29,750
is it possible to relocate Arnheid?

41
00:03:30,910 --> 00:03:34,330
No, I think we should
be careful right now.

42
00:03:35,210 --> 00:03:39,010
Once she wakes up,
I can see how she's doing,

43
00:03:39,710 --> 00:03:40,920
but at the moment

44
00:03:41,010 --> 00:03:45,300
I honestly can't determine her condition.

45
00:03:46,220 --> 00:03:49,430
And plus, I'm worried about her baby.

46
00:03:49,930 --> 00:03:52,730
The best thing we can do is let her rest.

47
00:03:53,230 --> 00:03:56,150
At least until she regains consciousness.

48
00:03:58,730 --> 00:04:00,280
One day…

49
00:04:00,780 --> 00:04:04,280
Let's wait for just one day
and see how it goes.

50
00:04:05,370 --> 00:04:07,120
Are you serious?

51
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:09,910
What are you going to do after that?

52
00:04:19,090 --> 00:04:20,880
Boss, hurry!

53
00:04:22,340 --> 00:04:24,130
-Are they here?
-Yes.

54
00:04:25,220 --> 00:04:26,840
Where I'm pointing.

55
00:04:32,060 --> 00:04:33,770
That was faster than I expected.

56
00:04:35,060 --> 00:04:38,940
Send a message to the master!
We spot a fleet in the north.

57
00:04:40,020 --> 00:04:43,320
The king's army is here.

58
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:21,580
-They're here.
-That's them.

59
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:23,920
-What should we do?
-First…

60
00:06:31,470 --> 00:06:33,640
You idiot! Don't shoot without permission!

61
00:06:34,220 --> 00:06:36,600
Obviously it won't reach at this distance!

62
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:39,480
Lure them in more and then at once--

63
00:06:52,870 --> 00:06:56,120
Damn it! Go back!

64
00:06:56,620 --> 00:06:58,040
Darn it!

65
00:06:58,620 --> 00:07:01,120
How are they reaching all the way here?

66
00:07:10,510 --> 00:07:13,640
Spread out and gain control over the area.

67
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:15,930
Make way for His Majesty The King.

68
00:07:26,980 --> 00:07:30,780
It seems as though
Ketil wants to fight me.

69
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:34,030
Dispatch an envoy, Wulf.

70
00:07:34,530 --> 00:07:37,990
We will line up here
and wait for Ketil's response.

71
00:07:38,080 --> 00:07:39,080
Yes, Your Majesty.

72
00:07:44,210 --> 00:07:48,250
This is a nice piece of land.
It's a waste to stain it with blood.

73
00:07:57,640 --> 00:08:01,350
Based on the aforementioned reasons,
King Canute

74
00:08:01,430 --> 00:08:04,350
has ordered to have
the rebellious Ketil and his family

75
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:08,820
be outlawed for ten years
from this day forward.

76
00:08:09,690 --> 00:08:13,360
Under normal circumstances,
these crimes are worthy of death,

77
00:08:13,450 --> 00:08:16,530
but the lives
of Ketil and his family are spared

78
00:08:16,620 --> 00:08:20,540
as a result of the mercy
of none other than His Majesty.

79
00:08:20,620 --> 00:08:23,040
Humbly accept your punishment.

80
00:08:25,670 --> 00:08:27,210
That is all.

81
00:08:27,290 --> 00:08:30,590
If you don't want to die,
hurry up and flee to another country.

82
00:08:30,670 --> 00:08:33,470
We will wait until tomorrow morning
for your answer.

83
00:08:41,310 --> 00:08:43,020
You're useless!

84
00:08:43,100 --> 00:08:45,230
How could you let them on shore so easily!

85
00:08:47,230 --> 00:08:50,230
Rebellion? Outlawry?

86
00:08:50,730 --> 00:08:53,860
Don't get cocky with me, you brat!

87
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:56,740
I'm back.

88
00:08:58,320 --> 00:09:01,740
Thorgil! How was Canute's army?

89
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:06,370
They were boiling their pots
and leisurely eating lunch.

90
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:10,340
<i>There are two warships</i>
<i>and two cargo ships.</i>

91
00:09:10,420 --> 00:09:13,260
<i>And they've pitched tents</i>
<i>right by the landing place.</i>

92
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:16,380
<i>They have approximately 100 men.</i>

93
00:09:18,220 --> 00:09:20,140
One hundred?

94
00:09:20,220 --> 00:09:23,390
Yeah, excluding the slaves and servants.

95
00:09:29,270 --> 00:09:30,690
-What a joke.
-Did you hear that?

96
00:09:30,770 --> 00:09:34,530
That is less than a third of our army.

97
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:38,860
That darn Canute…
Did he think that we would

98
00:09:38,950 --> 00:09:42,740
bow down in fear
once we saw the king himself?

99
00:09:42,830 --> 00:09:47,870
This land is home to countless daredevils
who aren't afraid of the king!

100
00:09:48,370 --> 00:09:50,960
Let's go, all of you!

101
00:09:51,040 --> 00:09:55,380
Whoever beheads the king
will receive a prize of their choice!

102
00:09:55,460 --> 00:09:56,800
Yeah!

103
00:09:56,880 --> 00:09:59,340
Yes!

104
00:09:59,430 --> 00:10:01,680
What a happy bunch.

105
00:10:03,850 --> 00:10:05,810
These 100 men aren't ordinary warriors.

106
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:10,230
The ones surrounding the large tent…

107
00:10:10,730 --> 00:10:12,820
Those are the king's thegns.

108
00:10:13,770 --> 00:10:17,280
Th… The king is seriously here?

109
00:10:18,530 --> 00:10:21,320
We're talking about the royal guard here.

110
00:10:21,410 --> 00:10:24,240
They're a group
of the strongest warriors in Denmark.

111
00:10:24,740 --> 00:10:27,160
And they're Thorgil's former
brothers-in-arms.

112
00:10:27,660 --> 00:10:31,460
S… So you mean…

113
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:35,590
all of them are as strong as Thorgil?

114
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:40,590
So what about the other guys
in white capes?

115
00:10:40,680 --> 00:10:43,140
Are they weaker
compared to the royal guard?

116
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:46,430
What? You've never seen them before?

117
00:10:47,730 --> 00:10:50,850
They are the Jomsvikings.

118
00:10:54,610 --> 00:10:58,400
I've never seen your eyes open so wide.

119
00:11:02,370 --> 00:11:04,830
We can't win.

120
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:11,370
They're on another level compared to
our hodgepodge of farmers and warriors.

121
00:11:11,870 --> 00:11:14,540
They're the kind of people
who only think about war,

122
00:11:14,630 --> 00:11:16,460
from morning to night.

123
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:21,840
But it seems like the master needs to
fight them once to understand that.

124
00:11:24,140 --> 00:11:26,470
If you want to run away, go ahead.

125
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:29,560
King Canute is giving us time to escape.

126
00:11:30,730 --> 00:11:33,650
What are you going to do, Boss?

127
00:11:34,650 --> 00:11:37,530
I'm a commander. How could I run away?

128
00:11:38,730 --> 00:11:41,780
I'll try my best to protect
as many as I can

129
00:11:41,860 --> 00:11:45,120
of those 350 overconfident dummies.

130
00:11:45,620 --> 00:11:47,660
Well then,

131
00:11:47,740 --> 00:11:52,250
why don't we tie up the Ketil family
and hand them over?

132
00:11:52,330 --> 00:11:55,290
That's right!
Then we won't have to go to war.

133
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:58,300
We're going to tie up Thorgil too?

134
00:11:58,380 --> 00:12:02,380
Don't be a chicken!
If eight of us go, we can manage.

135
00:12:02,470 --> 00:12:05,050
No, it's not just Thorgil.

136
00:12:05,680 --> 00:12:08,470
There's the rumored "Iron Fist Ketil."

137
00:12:08,560 --> 00:12:11,680
You know the story about
how he killed a bear with his bare hands.

138
00:12:15,150 --> 00:12:18,610
Come on, let's just run away, Boss!

139
00:12:18,690 --> 00:12:21,990
Nothing good is going to come
from being stubborn.

140
00:12:24,990 --> 00:12:26,660
"Iron Fist," huh?

141
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:31,290
I know Iron Fist very well.

142
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:35,710
<i>I met him when I was about 15 or 16.</i>

143
00:12:36,210 --> 00:12:39,170
<i>He showed me the ropes on the battlefield.</i>

144
00:12:39,670 --> 00:12:42,420
<i>He really was incredibly strong.</i>

145
00:12:43,970 --> 00:12:47,340
He's like an older brother to me.

146
00:12:49,930 --> 00:12:53,600
I forget how many years ago it was,
but I got into a little trouble

147
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:56,230
and I became a fugitive.

148
00:12:57,150 --> 00:13:00,440
<i>I thought my big brother, Ketil,</i>
<i>would be willing to take me in,</i>

149
00:13:00,940 --> 00:13:05,070
<i>so I followed the rumors</i>
<i>and fled to this farm.</i>

150
00:13:06,860 --> 00:13:08,490
<i>However,</i>

151
00:13:08,570 --> 00:13:11,660
<i>when I finally arrived here…</i>

152
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:15,830
Who are you? Do you have business with me?

153
00:13:17,170 --> 00:13:20,920
<i>It was a completely different person,</i>
<i>believe it or not.</i>

154
00:13:21,670 --> 00:13:22,710
Huh?

155
00:13:24,170 --> 00:13:25,930
What?

156
00:13:26,010 --> 00:13:27,590
What in the world!

157
00:13:28,590 --> 00:13:31,220
The master is deceiving everyone.

158
00:13:31,310 --> 00:13:34,350
Just because they happened to have
the same name.

159
00:13:36,100 --> 00:13:37,440
I'm speechless.

160
00:13:37,520 --> 00:13:40,230
How did no one find out until now?

161
00:13:40,810 --> 00:13:44,360
But it's not like I had
anywhere else to go.

162
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:47,990
So I ended up working here as a guard dog.

163
00:13:49,490 --> 00:13:52,540
They've fed me for free
for quite some time.

164
00:13:54,290 --> 00:13:57,620
It's about time
I pay them back for the food.

165
00:14:09,010 --> 00:14:11,220
Well, you guys can do whatever you like.

166
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:14,180
Now you know the master is a fraud

167
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:16,600
who isn't worth risking your life for.

168
00:14:19,810 --> 00:14:22,060
Well then, take care.

169
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:45,420
Don't try to act cool, you idiots.

170
00:14:45,500 --> 00:14:48,840
You guys will die before you get to
pay back for your meals.

171
00:14:48,920 --> 00:14:51,180
Sh… Shut up!

172
00:14:52,050 --> 00:14:54,680
If we dine and dash
against a fraud like him,

173
00:14:54,760 --> 00:14:58,730
that will make us
the real scum of the earth.

174
00:14:58,810 --> 00:15:01,730
We will work and pay for our food!

175
00:15:05,230 --> 00:15:08,940
<i>Don't go blabbering</i>
<i>about what I just told you.</i>

176
00:15:38,810 --> 00:15:40,770
Their backs are against the ocean.

177
00:15:41,270 --> 00:15:44,190
The king's army is positioned
in two lines here.

178
00:15:45,730 --> 00:15:47,520
This circle is King Canute.

179
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:50,900
They've docked their ships on the sand

180
00:15:50,990 --> 00:15:53,200
and are not thinking about
what's behind them.

181
00:15:54,490 --> 00:15:58,330
They know that we don't have
a sufficient army.

182
00:16:00,910 --> 00:16:04,880
The terrain is wide open
so we can't launch a surprise attack.

183
00:16:05,380 --> 00:16:07,960
Olmar, how would you attack them?

184
00:16:08,590 --> 00:16:09,880
Huh?

185
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:12,340
A night attack?

186
00:16:12,420 --> 00:16:13,630
Wrong.

187
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:17,050
Night attacks are done by
first-rate warriors.

188
00:16:17,140 --> 00:16:19,850
It's impossible for amateurs.

189
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:24,650
<i>Those guys won't be of any help.</i>

190
00:16:24,730 --> 00:16:27,110
<i>By the time you count to 100</i>
<i>they'll all be killed.</i>

191
00:16:27,770 --> 00:16:28,900
What?

192
00:16:28,980 --> 00:16:32,820
Then why did you assemble them?

193
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:36,490
You amateur.

194
00:16:37,070 --> 00:16:39,160
There's only one reason.

195
00:16:40,620 --> 00:16:42,830
So they can distract the king

196
00:16:42,910 --> 00:16:46,040
while we count to 100.

197
00:17:00,680 --> 00:17:04,100
Thorgil! Where are you, Thorgil?

198
00:17:05,270 --> 00:17:07,940
Jeez, where is he when I need him?

199
00:17:08,980 --> 00:17:11,480
Master, the entire army is ready.

200
00:17:11,570 --> 00:17:15,320
All right. On my order, get ready to fire.

201
00:17:16,450 --> 00:17:17,820
Get ready!

202
00:17:20,370 --> 00:17:23,200
Master, this is the final warning.

203
00:17:24,620 --> 00:17:26,290
If we do this, we'll lose.

204
00:17:27,370 --> 00:17:29,040
That's enough, Snake.

205
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:31,550
I am the Iron Fist Ketil.

206
00:17:31,630 --> 00:17:35,130
Nothing about me is inferior to that brat.

207
00:17:39,970 --> 00:17:41,760
Fire!

208
00:17:56,950 --> 00:17:58,200
It's begun.

209
00:18:02,580 --> 00:18:04,790
The best of luck, Pater.

210
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:08,290
Damn it!

211
00:18:13,090 --> 00:18:15,050
It's all right. Let's go.

212
00:18:16,010 --> 00:18:18,010
Both armies are in the middle of fighting.

213
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:22,550
Slowly! Try to keep it stable.

214
00:18:29,310 --> 00:18:32,020
I'm not going to be responsible for this…

215
00:18:32,110 --> 00:18:33,900
This is stealing, isn't it?

216
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:36,150
Stealing a slave…

217
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:38,070
Don't worry about it.

218
00:18:38,150 --> 00:18:40,320
I left a reasonable amount of money.

219
00:18:41,950 --> 00:18:44,790
I didn't know you had it in you, Dad.

220
00:18:45,490 --> 00:18:48,620
She's Thorfinn's friend.
I can't leave her behind.

221
00:18:49,120 --> 00:18:52,000
If she stays here, she will be killed.

222
00:18:58,550 --> 00:19:00,090
We couldn't

223
00:19:00,930 --> 00:19:02,930
say goodbye to the old master.

224
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:40,760
Did the children fall asleep?

225
00:19:45,760 --> 00:19:46,680
Yes.

226
00:19:48,470 --> 00:19:52,560
They fall asleep so quickly
when they're swayed by the wagon.

227
00:20:01,150 --> 00:20:02,450
Are you scared?

228
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:05,740
Don't worry.

229
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:08,790
We'll get out of this dark forest soon.

230
00:20:10,950 --> 00:20:15,130
This place is a pool of pain and despair.

231
00:20:15,630 --> 00:20:18,550
It's a forest with bloodthirsty beasts.

232
00:20:19,380 --> 00:20:22,220
It's not the place to raise a life.

233
00:20:25,300 --> 00:20:29,510
We have a warm home waiting for us.

234
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:34,810
It was a long, painful journey, wasn't it?

235
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:38,610
But that pain will soon end.

236
00:20:41,280 --> 00:20:42,110
Yes.

237
00:20:44,740 --> 00:20:46,070
I guess you're right.

238
00:21:00,880 --> 00:21:02,760
But even then,

239
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:06,550
there are still…

240
00:21:09,220 --> 00:21:13,310
beings who try to survive out here.

241
00:21:19,190 --> 00:21:20,480
Gardar?

242
00:21:22,730 --> 00:21:24,190
Go ahead

243
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:29,320
and say goodbye to those
who took care of you.

244
00:21:34,910 --> 00:21:38,880
I'll be waiting here with the children.

245
00:21:44,420 --> 00:21:45,800
You're right.

246
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:51,050
I have to say thank you
to Einar and everybody.

247
00:21:57,440 --> 00:21:59,520
Stop! Stop!

248
00:22:01,570 --> 00:22:03,730
It's me! Can you comprehend?

249
00:22:03,820 --> 00:22:04,860
How do you feel?

250
00:22:08,660 --> 00:22:10,910
Einar…

251
00:22:20,460 --> 00:22:23,960
Advance 50 steps! Be thorough.

252
00:22:24,460 --> 00:22:26,510
Show them the difference in power.

253
00:22:38,850 --> 00:22:41,770
As expected of the Jomsvikings.

254
00:22:41,860 --> 00:22:44,650
They only have one line of 70 men,

255
00:22:44,730 --> 00:22:46,400
but they're not faltering at all.

256
00:22:47,320 --> 00:22:49,740
At this point, we don't need a rear guard.

257
00:22:49,820 --> 00:22:53,120
Send the thegns in the second row
to arrest Ketil.

258
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:54,030
Yes, Your Majesty.

259
00:22:54,120 --> 00:22:57,540
Don't retreat! Charge!

260
00:22:57,620 --> 00:23:00,460
Show them your determination!

261
00:23:01,830 --> 00:23:03,250
Damn it!

262
00:23:03,340 --> 00:23:06,510
Where did my sons go?

263
00:23:22,230 --> 00:23:23,940
It's impossible

264
00:23:24,440 --> 00:23:27,570
to swim while carrying a sword.

265
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:36,200
It's impossible, brother.

266
00:23:38,160 --> 00:23:39,500
I can't

267
00:23:40,160 --> 00:23:43,460
become like you.

268
00:24:07,650 --> 00:24:11,530
You'll never see me coming, King Canute!

269
00:25:54,010 --> 00:25:55,050
<i>"Pain."</i>

270
00:25:55,130 --> 00:25:56,470
Subtitle translation by: Kiko Morita

